snippets.title: AccountIssueService listAccountIssues Sample
snippets.description: Lists all account issues of a Merchant Center account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getAccount Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves an account from your Merchant Center account. After inserting, updating, or deleting an account, it may take several minutes before changes take effect.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService createAndConfigureAccount Sample
snippets.description: Creates a standalone Merchant Center account with additional configuration. Adds the user that makes the request as an admin for the new account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService deleteAccount Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the specified account regardless of its type: standalone, MCA or sub-account. Deleting an MCA leads to the deletion of all of its sub-accounts. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateAccount Sample
snippets.description: Updates an account regardless of its type: standalone, MCA or sub-account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService listAccounts Sample
snippets.description: Lists accounts accessible to the calling user and matching the constraints of the request such as page size or filters. This is not just listing the sub-accounts of an MCA, but all accounts the calling user has access to including other MCAs, linked accounts, standalone accounts and so on.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService listSubAccounts Sample
snippets.description: List all sub-accounts for a given multi client account. This is a convenience wrapper for the more powerful `ListAccounts` method. This method will produce the same results as calling `ListsAccounts` with the following filter: `relationship(providerId={parent} AND service(type="ACCOUNT_AGGREGATION"))`

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getAccountTax Sample
snippets.description: Returns the tax rules that match the conditions of GetAccountTaxRequest

snippets.title: AccountIssueService listAccountTax Sample
snippets.description: Lists the tax settings of the sub-accounts only in your Merchant Center account. This method can only be called on a multi-client account, otherwise it'll return an error.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateAccountTax Sample
snippets.description: Updates the tax settings of the account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getBusinessIdentity Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the business identity of an account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateBusinessIdentity Sample
snippets.description: Updates the business identity of an account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getBusinessInfo Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the business info of an account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateBusinessInfo Sample
snippets.description: Updates the business info of an account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getEmailPreferences Sample
snippets.description: Returns the email preferences for a Merchant Center account user. Use the name=accounts/*/users/me/emailPreferences alias to get preferences for the authenticated user.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateEmailPreferences Sample
snippets.description: Updates the email preferences for a Merchant Center account user. MCA users should specify the MCA account rather than a sub-account of the MCA. Preferences which are not explicitly selected in the update mask will not be updated. It is invalid for updates to specify an UNCONFIRMED opt-in status value. Use the name=accounts/*/users/me/emailPreferences alias to update preferences for the authenticated user.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getHomepage Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a store's homepage.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateHomepage Sample
snippets.description: Updates a store's homepage. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService claimHomepage Sample
snippets.description: Claims a store's homepage. Executing this method requires admin access. If the homepage is already claimed, this will recheck the verification (unless the merchant is exempted from claiming, which also exempts from verification) and return a successful response. If ownership can no longer be verified, it will return an error, but it won't clear the claim. In case of failure, a canonical error message will be returned:    * PERMISSION_DENIED: user doesn't have the necessary permissions on this    MC account;    * FAILED_PRECONDITION:      - The account is not a Merchant Center account;      - MC account doesn't have a homepage;      - claiming failed (in this case the error message will contain more      details).

snippets.title: AccountIssueService unclaimHomepage Sample
snippets.description: Unclaims a store's homepage. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getOnlineReturnPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets an existing return policy.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService listOnlineReturnPolicies Sample
snippets.description: Lists all existing return policies.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getProgram Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the specified program for the account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService listPrograms Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves all programs for the account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService enableProgram Sample
snippets.description: Enable participation in the specified program for the account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService disableProgram Sample
snippets.description: Disable participation in the specified program for the account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getRegion Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a region defined in your Merchant Center account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService createRegion Sample
snippets.description: Creates a region definition in your Merchant Center account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateRegion Sample
snippets.description: Updates a region definition in your Merchant Center account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService deleteRegion Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a region definition from your Merchant Center account. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService listRegions Sample
snippets.description: Lists the regions in your Merchant Center account.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getShippingSettings Sample
snippets.description: Retrieve shipping setting information.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService insertShippingSettings Sample
snippets.description: Replace the shipping setting of a merchant with the request shipping setting. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getTermsOfServiceAgreementState Sample
snippets.description: Returns the state of a terms of service agreement.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService retrieveForApplicationTermsOfServiceAgreementState Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the state of the agreement for the application terms of service.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService getTermsOfService Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the `TermsOfService` associated with the provided version.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService retrieveLatestTermsOfService Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the latest version of the `TermsOfService` for a given `kind` and `region_code`.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService acceptTermsOfService Sample
snippets.description: Accepts a `TermsOfService`. Executing this method requires admin access.

snippets.title: AccountIssueService createUser Sample

snippets.title: AccountIssueService updateUser Sample
